SIMPLE: intertwine
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intertwine
<hw>In`ter*twine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To unite by
twining one with another; to entangle; to interlace.</def>
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intertwine</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Intertwine
<hw>In`ter*twine"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be twined or twisted
together; to become mutually involved or enfolded.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intertwine</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Intertwine
<hw>In`ter*twine"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
intertwining, or the state of being intertwined.</def>
<rj><au>Coleridge.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intertwiningly</ent>⟦br⟧
